<span class="thumb thumb--square"><span class="thumb__sizer"><span class="thumb__tugger"><img alt="" class=" thumb__image" play="false" src="https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/22173_254x191.jpg?" /><span class="thumb__aligner"></span></span></span></span>
</a>
<div class='talk-speaker__details media__message'>
<div class='talk-speaker__name h10'>
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/daniel_goleman">Daniel Goleman</a>
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__description'>
Psychologist
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__bio'>
Daniel Goleman, psychologist and award-winning author of Emotional Intelligence and other books on EI, challenges traditional measures of intelligence as a predictor of life success.
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/daniel_goleman">Full bio</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

